      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Dispatches from Washington, D.\nc., state that Judge WI. Gordon\nOF Spokane and other attorneys of\nthe Northwest have filed claims in\nconnection with the opening of the\nsouth half of the Colville reserva-\nton amounting to $4,000 These\nclaims are based upon a contract\nwith the Indians, said to have been\napproved by Hoke Smith, then Sec\nrotary of the interior. 1t is stated\nWashington officials will make a\nfight to prevent the lawyers getting\nanything out of the money going to\nthe redmen."
    }
